# Caddy reverse proxy (Section 5).
#
# The API is intentionally NOT exposed publicly: the Next.js app is the only
# client and reaches FastAPI over the internal Docker network (api:8000),
# attaching the backend key + enforcing the access gate in its server-side proxy
# routes (apps/web/app/api/**). Routing everything to the web app therefore
# keeps the credential injection and gate on the only public path — and upholds
# "the frontend never talks to rag_core directly" end to end.
#
# Caddy issues + renews Let's Encrypt certs automatically for SITE_DOMAIN.

{$SITE_DOMAIN} {
	encode gzip
	reverse_proxy web:3000
}
